    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are positioned for a high-ceiling outing today, led by the elite efficiency of **Jackson Merrill** (75.27) and **Kyle Tucker** (70.65). **Jackson Merrill** is our strongest play; hitting leadoff against Sean Burke, he benefits from a massive 10% boost for his spot in the order and a favorable 87% stolen base opportunity due to the pitcher's slow delivery. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** is in a prime spot against Michael McGreevy, where his ability to capitalize on a mid-4.00 xERA arm gives him significant upside despite neutral platoon conditions. **Drake Baldwin** rounds out our high-efficiency tier at 67.34, buoyed by an assumption of hitting second and a park factor that remains advantageous for his profile.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Coby Mayo**, who posted a respectable 52.17. While he matches up against the left-handed Ryan Weathers\u2014which historically boosts his utility\u2014he fell just short of the efficiency thresholds held by **Jacob Wilson** and **Josh Jung**. While **Gunnar Henderson** faces a tough platoon disadvantage against Weathers (a -15% hit to his score), his elite sprint speed and the \"Slow SP\" bonus attached to Weathers make him a mandatory start to chase the scarcity of stolen bases, ultimately pushing **Coby Mayo** to the pine.\n\nWe must remain vigilant regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" status for several key contributors like **Drake Baldwin**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Josh Jung**, **Dominic Smith**, **Josh Lowe**, **Andy Pages**, **Jackson Merrill**, and **Kyle Tucker**. These projections rely on historical slotting; any deviation in the actual batting order could necessitate a pivot to **Miguel Vargas** or **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, who are currently waiting in the wings with scores hovering near the 50-point mark. Additionally, while **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (58.22) is starting, we should temper expectations; he faces a stiff test against Prielipp, whose 3.34 xERA significantly degrades the base projection.",
